<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-29T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-29T23:00:00-05:00" n="238" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.91/9–3047: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-30T13:00:00+09:00">September
                                    30, 1947—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 29—11:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2316. USIS<note n="76" xml:id="d238fn1">United States Information
                                Service.</note> Chinese news editor states that Tso Shi-sen, Vice
                            Minister of Information for the Kuomintang, instructed
                            Kuomintang-controlled <pb facs="0308" n="298" xml:id="pg_298"/>
                            newspapers in Shanghai not to publish any criticism which American
                            officials or the American press levelled against Soviet Union unless
                            absolutely necessary, in which case news should be played down using
                            only short items under inconspicuous headlines. Instruction was sent to
                            all Kuomintang publishers and editors.</p>
                        <p>Sent Nanking 1624; repeated Department 2316.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>